---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Tiago Lobo">
	<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold" style={{ color: 'var(--text-heading)' }}>About</h1>

	<div class="mt-6 max-w-3xl space-y-4 leading-relaxed" style={{ color: 'var(--text-body)' }}>
		<p>
			I started out building mobile apps — Kotlin, MVVM, the kind of work where you ship a
			feature and watch someone use it on their phone the same week. That instinct for fast,
			visible feedback followed me into full-stack work: React and Node.js on the frontend and
			backend, Flutter and C#/.NET on other projects, PostgreSQL and MySQL underneath — enough
			breadth to be comfortable moving between mobile, web, and cloud without treating any one
			of them as "home."
		</p>
		<p>
			More recently that curiosity turned toward DevOps and AI — specifically, what happens
			when you point large language models at the unglamorous parts of shipping software:
			reviewing pull requests, generating and validating infrastructure as code, healing a
			Kubernetes cluster before a human has to. That's the work I do now, and the direction I
			want to keep going.
		</p>
		<p>
			Outside of client work, I volunteer with ANEIS (Association for the Study and
			Intervention in Giftedness) — which is also why I ended up building{' '}
			<a href="/projects/bits-bots" class="underline" style={{ color: 'var(--accent)' }}>Bits &amp; Bots</a>,
			a STEAM platform for gifted children, in my own time.
		</p>
	</div>

	<section class="mt-12">
		<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold" style={{ color: 'var(--text-heading)' }}>Experience</h2>
		<ul class="mt-6 space-y-6">
			<li>
				<p class="font-semibold" style={{ color: 'var(--text-heading)' }}>DevSecOps Engineer</p>
				<p class="text-sm" style={{ color: 'var(--text-muted)' }}>DevScope, Lda · Sep 2026 – Present</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p class="font-semibold" style={{ color: 'var(--text-heading)' }}>DevOps &amp; AI Intern</p>
				<p class="text-sm" style={{ color: 'var(--text-muted)' }}>DevScope, Lda · Feb – Jun 2026</p>
				<p class="mt-1 text-sm leading-relaxed" style={{ color: 'var(--text-body)' }}>
					Researched and implemented approaches to integrate Large Language Models into DevOps
					workflows, covering automated code review, Infrastructure as Code generation and
					validation, Kubernetes auto-healing, and CI/CD automation on Azure.
				</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p class="font-semibold" style={{ color: 'var(--text-heading)' }}>Mobile Developer Intern</p>
				<p class="text-sm" style={{ color: 'var(--text-muted)' }}>Eleven Systems · Feb – Jul 2023</p>
				<p class="mt-1 text-sm leading-relaxed" style={{ color: 'var(--text-body)' }}>
					Delivered major feature enhancements across four transport applications, including a
					Material Design 3 interface with Dark Mode, real-time bus tracking via the Google Maps
					API, offline favorites with Room Database, and a migration to a scalable MVVM
					architecture.
				</p>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="mt-12">
		<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold" style={{ color: 'var(--text-heading)' }}>Education</h2>
		<ul class="mt-6 space-y-4">
			<li>
				<p class="font-semibold" style={{ color: 'var(--text-heading)' }}>Computer Science &amp; Engineering, Degree</p>
				<p class="text-sm" style={{ color: 'var(--text-muted)' }}>
					Polytechnic Institute of Viseu (IPV) · 2023 – 2026 · Final Grade: 16.34 · Final Project: 19/20
				</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p class="font-semibold" style={{ color: 'var(--text-heading)' }}>Mobile Apps, CTESP</p>
				<p class="text-sm" style={{ color: 'var(--text-muted)' }}>Polytechnic Institute of Cávado and Ave (UPCA) · 2021 – 2023</p>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
